# AWS Configuration
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your_access_key
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your_secret_key
AWS_REGION=us-east-1

# Kubernetes Configuration
KUBECONFIG=~/.kube/config

# Application Configuration
DEVOPS_AUTOMATOR_CONFIG=~/.devops-automator/config.yaml
LOG_LEVEL=INFO

# Security
VAULT_ADDR=http://vault.example.com
VAULT_TOKEN=your_token

Plugin System
DevOps Automator features a modular plugin architecture:

Available Plugins
AWS Infrastructure - EC2, RDS, S3, VPC, IAM management

Kubernetes - Cluster operations, deployments, Helm

Docker - Image building, registry management

Monitoring - Prometheus, Grafana, AlertManager

Database - RDS, Cloud SQL, MongoDB

Security - IAM, Security Groups, compliance checks

Creating Custom Plugins


from src.plugins.base import BasePlugin

class CustomPlugin(BasePlugin):
    """Custom DevOps automation plugin."""
    
    def initialize(self, config: dict):
        """Initialize plugin."""
        self.config = config
    
    def execute(self, command: str, **kwargs):
        """Execute plugin command."""
        if command == 'custom-action':
            return self._custom_action(**kwargs)
        
        raise ValueError(f"Unknown command: {command}")
    
    def _custom_action(self, **kwargs):
        """Custom action implementation."""
        return {'success': True, 'result': 'Custom action completed'}
